Police in Anambra State has arrested a 21-year-old man who specializes in dispossessing commercial tricyclists of their tricycles. The suspect, Ikechukwu Eze, according to the spokesperson of Anambra State Police Command, SP Haruna Mohammed, was arrested at Ozubulu by men of the Nigeria Police Force who were working in conjunction with vigilante operatives in the area. Haruna also disclosed that the suspect who hails from Umudim in Nnewi was also arrested with a pump action gun and seven cartridges. This is suspected to be the arms with which he dispossesses the tricyclists of their tricycles. The release stating this read, “On the 28/11/2019 at about 02:30 am while on routine patrol, Police operatives attached to Ozubulu Division in conjunction with Vigilante group intercepted one Ikechukwu Eze ‘m’ aged 21 years of Okpuneme village Umudim, Nneni with a tricycle (Keke-Napep)bearing plate number PHC 541 QV. “Search was conducted on the tricycle leading to the recovery of one Pump Action gun and Seven live cartridges. “Investigation revealed that suspect allegedly snatched the Keke at gunpoint from one Munachi Dike ‘m’ of Awada Obosi at Onitsha Owerri Expressway before Oba junction. “Consequently, suspect has confessed to the crime voluntarily and would be charged to court as soon as investigation is concluded.” Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.